methods.entireTable:
Request a full snapshot of the data and populate a BarrageTable with the data that is received.

:return: (io.deephaven.extensions.barrage.table.BarrageTable) the BarrageTable
methods.partialTable:
**Incompatible overloads text - text from the first overload:**

Request a partial snapshot of the data limited by viewport or column set and populate a BarrageTable with
 the data that is received.

*Overload 1*  
  :param viewport: (io.deephaven.engine.rowset.RowSet) - the position-space viewport to use for the snapshot
  :param columns: (java.util.BitSet) - the columns to include in the snapshot
  :return: (io.deephaven.extensions.barrage.table.BarrageTable) the BarrageTable
  
*Overload 2*  
  :param viewport: (io.deephaven.engine.rowset.RowSet) - the position-space viewport to use for the snapshot
  :param columns: (java.util.BitSet) - the columns to include in the snapshot
  :param reverseViewport: (boolean) - Whether to treat posRowSet as offsets from #size() rather than 0
  :return: (io.deephaven.extensions.barrage.table.BarrageTable) the BarrageTable
